Package org.jretrofit

JRetrofit is a library which allows runtime addition of interfaces to classes which don't actually implement them.

          Description

Interface Summary
Retrofitter Implementations of this interface create retrofitted objects.

Retrofit This class has static shortcut methods to create retrofitted objects with the least possible amount of code.
RetrofitterWithMethodLookupCaching A Retrofitter implementation which caches method lookup.

AllMethodsNotImplementedException This exception is thrown if you try to use complete retrofitting, but your target object does not "implement" all of the required methods.

Package org.jretrofit Description

JRetrofit is a library which allows runtime addition of interfaces to classes which don't actually implement them. See the website documentation for tutorials and examples.
